This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with an extension of the Lasso algorithm for feature selection. It may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it discusses the optimization of a penalized problem. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of algorithms for optimization. The paper also mentions the use of the breast cancer gene expression data set, which suggests it could be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
